Plug-in name: Security-slicing
Plug-in shortname: security-slicing
Description: security slicing (experimental, undocumented)

Most options of the form '-security-slicing-option-name'
and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-security-slicing-no-option-name'.

Most options of the form '-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-no-option-name'.

Options taking a string as argument should preferably be written
-option-name="argument".

***** LIST OF AVAILABLE OPTIONS:

-security-slicing   perform the security slicing analysis (opposite option is
                    -no-security-slicing)

*** DEBUG

-security-slicing-debug <n>  level of debug for plug-in Security-slicing
                    (default to 0)

*** GETTING INFORMATION

-security-slicing-help  help of plug-in Security-slicing
-security-slicing-h  alias for option -security-slicing-help

*** OUTPUT MESSAGES

-security-slicing-log <K_1:file_1,...>  copy log messages from
                    Security-slicing to a file. <K> is a combination of these
                    characters:
                    a: ALL messages (equivalent to 'dfiruw')
                    d: debug       e: user or internal error (same as 'iu')
                    f: feedback    i: internal error
                    r: result      u: user error    w: warning
                    An empty <K> (e.g. ":file.txt") defaults to 'iruw'. One
                    plug-in can output to several files and vice-versa.
                    (preferably use -security-slicing-log="K_1:file_1,...")
-security-slicing-msg-key <k1[,...,kn]>  enables message display for
                    categories <k1>,...,<kn>. Use -security-slicing-msg-key
                    help to get a list of available categories, and * to
                    enable all categories (preferably use
                    -security-slicing-msg-key="k1[,...,kn]")
-security-slicing-verbose <n>  level of verbosity for plug-in
                    Security-slicing (default to 1)
-security-slicing-warn-key <k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]>  set warning status for
                    category <k1> to <s1>,...,<kn> to <sn>. Use
                    -security-slicing-warn-key help to get a list of
                    available categories, and * to enable all categories.
                    Possible statuses are inactive, feedback, warning, error,
                    abort, feedback-once, warning-once, error-once. Defaults
                    to warning. (preferably use
                    -security-slicing-warn-key="k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]")
